# Zymbly upload monorepo

## Layout

- `client/` — React 18 + TypeScript + webpack + styled-components (port 3000)
- `server/` — Express + multer upload API (port 3001)
- Root `package.json` uses npm workspaces

## Commands

- `npm install` from repo root
- `npm run dev` — starts client and server together
- `npm run build` — production client build
- `npm run start:server` — API only

## Conventions

- Never commit files under `server/uploads/`
- Prefer shared components in `client/src/components/` over page-local styled blocks
- All uploads go through `client/src/services/uploadService.ts`
- Use theme tokens from `client/src/theme/theme.ts` — no magic hex colors in components
- Workflow choices use `SelectBox`, not radio button groups
- Guided uploads use `GuidedUploadLayout` + `UploadStepSection` + `useGuidedUpload`
- Maintenance log capture (`/logs`) uses `logService.ts` + TanStack Query hooks in `hooks/logs/`; ingest fires on stop recording
